any tips for job interviews i've worked before but mostly babysitting or at my dad's business i want to interview for a job at this health club near my house but i don't really know how to do a good interview tips tricks plznthx just smile be polite be yourself and answer whatever questions they ask you honestly at my first job interview for a movie theater the boss asked me what my favorite thing about myself was and what my least favorite thing was most of the questions you'll get other than employment information will be about your personality also you want to dress appropriately maybe even dress up a little use good manners shake the hand of the interviewer be happy to be there show that you're interested using proper english is also a big plus don't ask about pay or hours unless the job is offered to you and don't forget to take all of your information references resume id and social security card good luck Social rule Shaggy dog story Jennifer Lopez Plame affair Humphrey Bogart Ken Jennings Customs and etiquette of Japan Friends Karl Rove U.S. presidential election debates, 2004 Marilyn Monroe Have I Got News For You The Grim Adventures of Billy and Mandy Mojave people Game show Dead Like Me Password The Adventures of Pete & Pete Interview Joke The SpongeBob SquarePants Movie Job interview Sydney Riot of 1879 Ocean's Twelve The Emancipation of Mimi Labor theory of value Current teachings of Prem Rawat Military opposition to the Reconciliation, Tolerance, and Unity Bill (Fiji) Singapore gay equality movement Scientology beliefs and practices Surplus value Knots Landing Theory of conduct Care Bears Dream Job (Season 2) The Fairly OddParents Minimum wage EastEnders Economics Great Teacher Onizuka The Apprentice 2 Teresa Heinz Kerry Calvin and Hobbes Practices of Jehovah's Witnesses The Simpsons 138th Episode Spectacular Samuel Goldwyn American Psycho Milton H. Erickson Constitution of the Turkish Republic of Northern Cyprus Unemployment $ale of the Century Kyle B